Therapeutic treatment and management of severe respiratory viral infections.

Vitamin D (250 micro grams/day; 0.5mg)
Zinc (50-100 mg/day)
Vitamin C (3000mg/day)
Flavanoids (200mg/day)
Vitamin A (3-6mg/day)
Vitamin E (500mg/day)

Diet/Nutrition/Management:
Great leafy vegetables and fruits
Turmeric Milk (with pinch of pepper)
Gooseberry
Ginger-garlic-turmeric-pepper- concoction

Nebulisation
Sun bathing
Breathing exercises
Take rest
Drink only warm liquids
AVOID SUGAR

Thank you.

snippet.textDisplay:
Even if so many don't want to understand, the corona delusion is a hysteria created by the * irresponsible ***, whether out of ignorance or evil intent I can't
final judgement. If we were to observe the annual waves of influenza just as closely, we would have comparable infection patterns. Let's not get crazy,
we urge politicians to finally get life back to normal. There is neither an overload of hospitals nor a danger for the whole world. The different
Death rates are mainly due to country-specific hygiene conditions. Anyone who talks to doctors will get this confirmed. Hygiene is always important.
When a certain level of human contamination has been reached, the virus will die. If we lock everyone away, only the course will be prolonged. The fear of politics is absolutely unfounded and understandable.
P.S. I belong to the so-called risk group due to pre-existing illnesses and I also protect myself against every wave of flu. The virus is only transmitted via the mucous membranes,
i.e. droplet infection through close contact and/or e.g. through shopping trolleys (whose handles are never cleaned), ... and thus transmission to the mouth/nose.
People, do NOT let yourselves be driven crazy and with all the strength and responsibility that we as citizens have for ourselves, our loved ones and our country, finally push back to the
to find the way back to normality.

snippet.textDisplay: I wonder if any of the governments around the world (including our country the U.S.) have thought of starting to convert warehouses into temporary hospitals? I wouldn't think it would matter where those warehouses are located because if it's helpful in trying to keep the hospitals from overflowing with patient then I say go for it! I'm no doctor but I hope the governments have at least considered if that plan would be feasible or not. If it's not feasible then fine but at least you have considered it. Another question to add on to that: if it's feasible, could one put some of the patients that are not in danger of dying into said houses? If there's someone on here from the medical and scientific fields, I wouldn't mind getting an education on this particular issue. Actually, it would be welcome! 😊 Take care everyone.

snippet.textDisplay:
This is the perfect time for people to focus on the spiritual and search our hearts. Now is the correct time to start reading your bible and researching who God is and how to make it into His Kingdom while you still have time to inquire. This virus is a wake up call. Its showing us all how fragile our lives really are and that none of us have enough time on this planet to take our futures lightly. This life is temporary. If Corona doesn't kill you, age will eventually. Search for Christ while you still have breath and He will reveal Himself to you. If you ignore Him, He will ignore you. This life is a test to see who is worthy of immortality, and as with all test, this test will eventually end. Those who pass will receive eternal life in the next world, so why not pass the test with flying colors?

Isaiah 55:6 "Seek the LORD while He may be found; call on Him while He is near. Let the wicked man forsake his own way and the unrighteous man his own thoughts; let him return to the LORD, that He may have compassion, and to our God, for He will freely pardon.…"

Matthew 10:32, 33 "Therefore everyone who confesses Me before men, I will also confess him before My Father in heaven. But whoever denies Me before men, I will also deny him before My Father in heaven."

John 3:16 "For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life."
